 risk, specialists from policy and practice alongside academics in different areas of children’s services consider progress in improving child protection arrangements, in transforming services and the challenges that remain. Local Safeguarding Children Boards (LSCBs), the statutory bodies responsible for local scrutiny of child protection arrangements, are now subject to Ofsted inspection and this publication considers the role of LSCBs, how services should respond to the most vulnerable children and what 'good' services look like.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aChild welfarezGreat Britain. 0aChildrenxServices forzGreat Britain. 0aInteragency coordinationzGreat Britain. 0aSocial work with childrenzGreat Britain. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Social Work.2bisacsh1 aBlyth, Maggie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrandon, Marian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrazil, Eleanor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClifton, Jenny, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFeatherstone, Brid, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGurrey, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHedges, Charlie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHicks, Leslie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJones, Ray, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMorris, Kate, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMunro, Eileen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPearce, Jenny J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPratt, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabular